    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Rear differential fluid Check"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "620_3.0_jpn_11581944_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "With the vehicle in a horizontal position, remove the filler bolt (A) and inspect that there is oil at the same level as the underside of the screw. If insufficient, add the specified \"Honda Genuine Ultra HGO-μ (hypoid gear oil)\" through the filler bolt holes until the level is the same as the level of the underside of the screw. Install the new sealing washer (B) and tighten the filler bolt."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "In case of insufficient oil, oil leakage from oil seals, drain bolts, or case joints may be the cause. Make sure that there is no abnormality in any part and replenish oil."
      ]
    }
  ],
